activityList.description: Hilly. Foggy. Felt tired from the start. 17 miles for the week.
Windy on the way out. 17 mph.
Feeling rested. 6:37, 6:26, 6:23, 6:22, 6:26, 6:40. Strava shows 40:15 for 10K and 19:53 for 5K. 43 bpm for the low overnight heart rate. I saw 39 around 1 pm before my run. Doesn’t seem right.
Shaking’ out. Merry Christmas! 22 miles for the week.
Too quick for a rest day. 19.9 miles for the week.
I did a fartlek the 3rd mile. 6:42, 6:27, 5:53. 19:51 for 5K. 3:35 for 1K.
Tired from yesterday. Easy build.

This was s good one. 30 degrees, 15 mph wind. Mile splits: 6:32, 6:21, 6:31, 6:34, 6:23, 6:25. 19:55.64 for 5K. 40:10 for 10K, I think Garmin gypped me out of the 10K time. An eagle flew over the house as I finished.
Cold. 18 mph wind. 12 degrees with the wind chill. Tired I think. The watch reset as it saved again.
I was afraid the first mile would set the tone. I felt tired and slow after a few days off. Loosened up after that. 41:41 for 10K.
It always seems faster at night. It felt good. About 8 second negative splits between miles.
I need to watch my left Achilles. Seems to warm up and feel okay a couple miles into the run.
Felt pretty good and rested. 44 bpm for my overnight resting heart rate.
Felt really good and under control. Tall and light. 20:31 for 5K. 41:52 for 10K.
Easy day. Need to pay attention to how my calves feel.
I need to slow down.
Tried a different 6 mile route with a big hill. Felt good. Nicer weather.

Felt terrible. 22MPH wind out of the west. Out and back, into the wind the first half. 6:39 and 6:45 for the first two miles. It felt slow but I must have overcompensated because of how it felt. Almost 20 miles for the week.
Cold. 22 MPH out of the NNW.
Felt really good. Felt light and tall. 6:50, 6:37, 6:37. Warmer today.
42:16 for 10K (6:43, 6:41, 6:34, 6:42, 6:40, 6:50). Tied with 11/7/2021 (6:43, 6:28, 6:41, 6:43, 6:42, 7:03) for fastest time. It’s surprising to run the exact same time.
First run since some sick days this weekend. It felt pretty good considering. Fastest mile was 6:33.
42:16 for 10K. 20:31 for 5K. 6:28 for the second mile. The last two miles were rough.
First mile was a bit fast. 6:43. Each mile was slower. Ending in a seven minute mile.
Cooler and windy this week.
Hilly. I’m not used to that. I started before sunrise.
I’m not sure what happened. An extra mile was added go my total. My phone restarted after I stopped at 3 miles.
My breathing felt a little behind early. I ran how I felt and didn’t look at my pace at all. Fastest 5K (21:02) and first 10K (42:25) since—who knows.
This was a good one. I ran my 1st mile in 6:39, which was a bit fast. I was able to recover and felt good throughout the run.
Windy. Really good. I felt better today than I have in quite some time. My first mile was in 6:51, my 2nd mile was in 6:42, and my last mile was in 6:29.

Beautiful day. I wanted to keep things controlled and slower the first two miles but didn’t. My calf felt pretty good but I am still trying to be careful. Between my last run and today I used a roller, which seemed to help loosen things up.
My calf felt good throughout. There is only a little tightness towards the end but nothing I was too concerned about. I iced for seven minutes in a 5 gallon bucket following the run.
Not great. I’ve taken some time off to recover from a calf injury. I got 3/4 of a mile into my run and started to feel it all again. I walked and jogged back home. More time off is needed.
My right calf balled up almost a mile into my normal 3 miler. During my last run it tightened up a bit towards the end but I didn’t think it was much of a concern. Walked home.
Kind of rough. 86 degrees at 9 pm. Got behind early. Night runs always feel faster than they are. I wanted to try something faster but it was forced.
Easy beginning and end with the dog. Let it go in the middle while she ran around the soccer fields. 6:26 for the middle mile.
Warm today. Last mile was slower again. Trying to keep HR in range.

6:39 for the first two miles. Vertigo came back last week so I wasn’t sure how good this would feel. I tried to take it down and match the last mile. Probably too quick the first two after a few days off.

Hello to anyone viewing these activities! 

Today’s run was hot. It was 85° when I finished. The last mile was a bit slow but I decided to add three strides and rests in the last half mile.
This felt really good. Heart rate became elevated at the last mile after I had picked up the pace to under 6:00/mi.
The first mile felt stiff. After the run I stopped and rest it for a few minutes and then did four strides.

Ran on the cross country course at Marshalltown Community College. It was a bit earlier than I expected especially going into the last mile. Ran with some running friends from high school, a reunion for past runners.
Started too fast, but felt really good early on.

Good but hot. I had seven or eight second positive splits for each mile. Sometime after the first half mile I started to catch up with a doe and a fawn along the trail. I started out with a 100 for a body battery, I was well rested this morning. Set ups and push-ups.
The best I’ve felt since vertigo.
I felt a lot better today. I felt more rested. Less miles slower but I wanted to keep my heart rate under control as much as possible.
This run felt a little more difficult than Monday. It felt good to start which meant I probably started out a little too quickly. My slowest split was the last mile.
It was hot!
3:41 for 1K. 6:07 for 1 mile.
